quran[399]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"He said, \"What is your errand then, O Messengers"
  51,32,"They said, \"Surely we are sent to a guilty people"
  51,33,That we may send down upon them stone of clay (or brimstones)
  51,34,Sent forth from your Lord for the extravagant (those who transgress beyond bounds)
  51,35,Then We brought forth such believers as were therein
  51,36,But We found not therein but one house of those who had Surrendered (Muslims)
  51,37,And We left therein a sign for those who fear the grievous penalty
  51,38,And in Moses (was another sign). When We sent him to Pharaoh with clear authority
  51,39,"But he turned away with his forces and said, \"A sorcerer or a mad man"
  51,40,So We seized him and his hosts and hurled them into the sea and his was the blame
  51,41,And in A´ad (was another sign). When We sent upon them the destructive wind
  51,42,"It spared naught on which it blew, but made it like dust"
  51,43,"And in Thamud (was another sign). When it was said to them, \"Enjoy yourselves for a while"
  51,44,"But they revolted against the commandment of their Lord, so the rumbling (thunderbolt or stunning noise of an earthquake) overtook them while they looked"
  51,45,"And they were not able to rise up, nor could they defend themselves"
  51,46,"And the people of Noah (were also a sign) before that, surely they were a transgressing people"
  51,47,"And the heaven, We raised it high with power, and it is We that expand the vastness of space (or We are the expanders of it)"
  51,48,"And the earth, We have spread it out; how gracious was the Spreader thereof"
  51,49,"And of all things have We created pairs, that you may reflect (or receive instruction)"
  51,50,"Therefore flee unto Allah, surely I am a plain Warner to you from Him"
  51,51,"And set not up with Allah another God: surely I am a plain Warner to you from Him"
  51,52,"Thus there did not come to those before them a messenger but they said, \"(He is) A sorcerer or a mad man"
  51,53,Is this the legacy (or tradition) they have transmitted to each other? Nay! They are a people extravagant (transgressing beyond bounds)
  51,54,Then turn your back upon them for you are not to blame
  51,55,"And continue to teach (or remind), for surely the reminder profits the believers"
  51,56,And I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship (serve) Me
  51,57,"No sustenance do I require from them, nor do I require that they should feed Me"
  51,58,"Surely it is Allah Who is the Bestower of sustenance, the Lord of Power, the ever Steadfast"
  51,59,"And lo! Those who do wrong shall have a portion like the portion of those of earlier generations, therefore let them not ask Me to hasten"
  51,60,Woe to those who disbelieve because of their Day which they are promised
  52,1,(I swear) By the Mount
  52,2,By a Decree inscribed
  52,3,"On a fine parchment, unrolled"
  52,4,And the much visited House
  52,5,And the canopy exalted
  52,6,And the swollen sea
  52,7,Most surely the doom of your Lord will come to pass
  52,8,There shall be none to avert it
  52,9,On the day when the heaven shall heave with awful commotion
  52,10,And the mountains shall move with awful movement
  52,11,Then woe on that Day unto the deniers (of the truth)
  52,12,Those who sport in vain discourses
  52,13,The Day on which they shall be driven irresistibly to the Fire of Hell
  52,14,This is the Fire which you used to deny
  52,15,"Is it magic then, or do you not see"
  52,16,"Burn you therein, and whether you bear it patiently or not, it makes no difference; you shall be requited only what you did"
  52,17,Surely those who guard (against evil) shall be in Gardens of Bliss
  52,18,"Rejoicing because of what their Lord gave them, and their Lord saved them from the punishment of the burning Fire"
  52,19,Eat and drink with profit and health because of what you did
  52,20,"Reclining on thrones set in ranks, and We will unite them to large-eyed beautiful ones (Houri)"
  52,21,"And as for those who believe and whose offspring follow them in faith, We will unite with them their offspring and We will not deprive them of naught of their work; each individual is a pledge for his own deeds"
  52,22,And We will provide them with fruit and flesh such as they desire
  52,23,They shall pass from one to another a cup wherein there shall be nothing vain nor any sin
  52,24,"And round them shall serve youth devoted to them, handsome as well-guarded (preserved or hidden) pearls"
  52,25,"And some of them shall draw near unto others, inquiring"
  52,26,"Saying, \"Surely in the past we feared for our families"
  52,27,But Allah has been gracious to us and He has saved us from the punishment of the Scorching Wind
  52,28,"Surely we called upon Him before: Surely He is the Benign, the Merciful"
  52,29,"Therefore continue you (O Muhammad) to remind (or warn), for by the grace of your Lord, you are not a soothsayer, or a madman"
  52,30,"Or do they say, \" (he is) A poet, for whom we await a calamity of (or an accident of or caused by) time"
  52,31,"Say, \"Wait (expect) ye! I too with you am waiting (expecting)"
  52,32,Nay! Do their understandings bid them this? Or are they a people transgressing beyond bounds
  52,33,"Or do they say, \"He has forged it.\" Nay! They will not believe"
  52,34,Then let them bring an announcement (or recital) like it if they are truthful
  52,35,"Or were they created out of nothing, or are they themselves the creators"
  52,36,Or did they create the heavens and the earth? Nay! They have no certainty
  52,37,Or have they the treasures of your Lord with them? Or have they been set in absolute authority
  52,38,Or have they a ladder (unto heaven) the means by which they listen? Then let their listener bring a clear authority
  52,39,Or has He daughters while you have sons
  52,40,"Or do you ask them for a reward, so that they are overburdened by a debt"
  52,41,Or have they the unseen so that they write it down
  52,42,Or do they desire to plot (or ensnare)? But those who disbelieve shall be the vanquished in their plot
  52,43,Or have they a God other than Allah? Glory be to Allah from what they set up (with Him)
  52,44,"And if they should see a portion of the heaven coming down, they would say, \"Piled up clouds"
  52,45,Leave them then till they meet that Day of theirs wherein they shall be made to swoon (with terror)
  52,46,"The day on which their struggle shall not avail them aught, nor shall they be helped"
  52,47,"And surely those who are unjust shall have a punishment besides that (in the world), but most of them understand not"
  52,48,"And wait patiently for the decree (command, judgment) of your Lord, for verily you are in Our eyes; and hymn the praise of your Lord when you rise"
  52,49,"And in the night, give Him glory too, and at the retreat of the stars"
  53,1,(I swear) By the star when it sets
  53,2,"Your companion (Muhammad) does not err, nor is he deceived (or astray or is misled)"
  53,3,Nor does he speak out of (his own) desire
  53,4,It (the Quran) is naught but revelation that is inspired (sent down to him)
  53,5,"Taught by one of mighty power, (The Archangel Gabriel)"
  53,6,Endowed with wisdom; for he appeared in clear vision
  53,7,While he was in the highest part of the horizon
  53,8,"Then he drew near, and descended"
  53,9,Until he was two bows distant or closer still
  53,10,And He revealed to His servant what He revealed
  53,11,The heart (of the Prophet) lied not in (making him see) what he saw
  53,12,What! Do you then dispute with him as to what he saw
  53,13,And certainly he saw him in another descent
  53,14,At the Lote-tree of the furthest boundary
  53,15,Near which is the Garden of Abode (or Presence)
  53,16,When that which shrouds (in mystery) covered the Lote-tree
  53,17,"The eye did not swerve, nor did it exceed the limit (or was over bold or went wrong)"
  53,18,Certainly he saw of the Greatest Signs of his Lord
  53,19,Have you seen Lat and Uzza
  53,20,"And Manat, the third, the last"
  53,21,What! For you the males and for Him the females
  53,22,This indeed is an unjust division
  53,23,"They are naught but names which you have named, you and your fathers; Allah has not sent for them any authority. They follow naught but conjecture and the low desires which their souls incline to, even though true guidance has come to them from their Lord"
  53,24,Or shall man have whatever whims he wishes
  53,25,Nay! To Allah belongs the after and the former life (or the End and the Beginning)
  53,26,"And how many so ever angels are in the heavens, their intercession does not avail at all except after Allah has given permission to whom He wills and chooses to accept"
  53,27,Most surely they who do not believe in the Hereafter name the angels with female names
  53,28,"And they have no knowledge of it; they do not follow anything but conjecture, and surely conjecture does not avail against the truth at all"
  53,29,"Therefore, turn aside from him who turns his back upon Our reminder (or remembrance) and does not desire anything but the life of this world"
  53,30,That is their sum of knowledge; surely your Lord knows best him who goes astray from His path and He knows best him who follows the right direction
  53,31,"And to Allah belongs that which is in the heavens and that which is in the earth, that He may reward those who do evil according to what they do, and that He may reward those who do good with goodness"
  53,32,"Those who keep aloof from the great sins and the indecencies, except the passing idea (or the unwilling or small offence); surely your Lord is liberal in forgiving. He knows you best when He brings you forth from the earth and when you are embryos in the"
  53,33,Have you then seen him who turns his back
  53,34,And gives a little and then withholds
  53,35,Has he the knowledge of the unseen so that he can see (the future or the hidden)
  53,36,"Or, has he not been informed of what is in the scriptures of Moses"
  53,37,And of Abraham who fulfilled (the commandments or duties)
  53,38,That no bearer of burdens shall bear the burden of another
  53,39,And that man shall have nothing but what he strives for
  53,40,And that his striving shall be seen
  53,41,Then shall he be rewarded for it with the fullest reward
  53,42,And that your Lord is the final goal
  53,43,And that He it is Who makes men laugh and makes them weep
  53,44,And that He it is Who causes death and gives life
  53,45,"And that He created pairs, the male and the female"
  53,46,From the small seed when it is placed (or lodged)
  53,47,And that on Him depends (or He has ordained) the bringing forth a second time
  53,48,And that He it is Who enriches and gives satisfaction (or fulfilment)
  53,49,And that He is the Lord of Sirius
  53,50,And that He did destroy the A´ad of old
  53,51,And Thamud He spared not
  53,52,And the people of Noah before them; surely they were most unjust and insolent transgressors
  53,53,And He destroyed the Overthrown Cities (of Sodom and Gomorrah)
  53,54,So that they were covered with that which covers
  53,55,Then about which of your Lord´s gifts will you dispute
  53,56,This is a Warner of (the series or like) the Warners of old
  53,57,The threatened event (or Hour) draws nigh
  53,58,There is none besides Allah to disclose (or actualise) it
  53,59,Marvel you then at this announcement
  53,60,And will you laugh and not weep
  53,61,While you are indulging in vanities
  53,62,So make obeisance (or prostrations) to Allah and serve Him
  54,1,The hour drew nigh (or is nigh) and the moon was rent in twain (or is rent)
  54,2,"And if they see a Sign they turn aside and say, \"Transient magic"
  54,3,"And they call it a lie, and follow their own low desires; but every affair has its appointed term"
  54,4,And certainly some narratives have come to them wherein is a deterrent
  54,5,Consummate wisdom - but warnings avail not
  54,6,So turn your back on them for the Day when the Summoner summons them unto a terrible affair
  54,7,"With downcast eyes, they come forth from their graves as if they were scattered locusts"
  54,8,"Hastening towards the Summoner. The unbelievers shall say, \"This is a hard day"
  54,9,"Before them the people of Noah rejected, yea they reject Our servant and called him mad, and he was driven away"
  54,10,"Therefore he called upon his Lord, \"I am overcome, come you then to help"
  54,11,So We opened the gates of heaven with water pouring forth
  54,12,And We caused water to gush forth from the land in springs; so the waters gathered together and rose according to a measure already ordained
  54,13,And We bore him on that (the Ark) which was made of planks and nails (or ties of palm-fibre)
  54,14,"Floating before Our eyes, a reward for him who was rejected"
  54,15,"And certainly We left it as a sign, but is there anyone that remembers (or takes heed)"
  54,16,How great was then My punishment after My warning
  54,17,"And certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will heed"
  54,18,"A´ad treated the truth as a lie, so how great was My punishment after My warning"
  54,19,Surely We sent on them a tornado in a day of violent disaster
  54,20,Tearing men away as if they were the trunks of palm-trees uprooted
  54,21,How great was then My punishment after My warning
  54,22,"And certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will heed"
  54,23,Thamud rejected the warning
  54,24,"So they said, \"What! A single mortal from among us! Shall we follow him? Most surely we shall then be in sure error and madness"
  54,25,Can it be that the reminder has been sent to him of all the people among us? Nay! He is an insolent liar
  54,26,"Ah, tomorrow shall they know who is the liar, the insolent one"
  54,27,"Surely We shall send them the she-camel as a trial; therefore, watch them and have patience"
  54,28,And inform them that the water is to be shared between them; every drinking shall be regulated
  54,29,"But they called their companion, who took (the sword) and hamstrung her"
  54,30,How great was then My punishment after My warning
  54,31,"Surely We sent upon them a single Shout (or Blast), so they became like the dry stubble which the maker of an enclosure collects"
  54,32,"And certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will heed"
  54,33,The people of Lot treated the warning. as a lie
  54,34,"Surely We sent upon them a storm with stones, except Lot´s followers; We saved them a little before daybreak"
  54,35,A favour from Us; thus do We reward him who gives thanks
  54,36,"And certainly he (Lot) warned them of Our violent punishment, but they obstinately disputed the warning"
  54,37,"And they endeavoured to snatch away his guests from him, but We blinded their eyes; \"So taste you My chastisement and My warning"
  54,38,And early in the morning a lasting chastisement overtook them
  54,39,So taste you My chastisement after My warning
  54,40,"And certainly We have made the Quran easy for remembrance, but is there anyone who will heed"
  54,41,And certainly the warning came to Pharaoh´s people
  54,42,"They rejected all Our Signs, so We overtook them with such a penalty as comes from One Mighty, Powerful"
  54,43,"Are the unbelievers of yours (O Quraish) better than these, or is there an exemption for you in the Sacred Books"
  54,44,"Or do they say, \"We are a host allied together to help each other"
  54,45,"But soon shall the hosts be routed, and they shall flee"
  54,46,"Nay, the Hour is their promised time, and the Hour shall be most grievous and bitter"
  54,47,Surely it is the guilty who are in error and madness
  54,48,"On the day when they shall be dragged upon their faces into the Fire, \"Taste the touch of hell"
  54,49,Surely We have created everything according to a measure
  54,50,"And Our command is but one, as the twinkling of an eye"
  54,51,"And certainly We have already destroyed the likes of you, but is there anyone who will heed"
  54,52,And everything they did is in the Scriptures (or the Record)
  54,53,And everything small and great is recorded
  54,54,Surely the righteous (who guard against evil) shall dwell among Gardens and Rivers
  54,55,Established in the Assembly of Truth in the presence of an Omnipotent Sovereign
  55,1,The Beneficent Allah
  55,2,Taught (Has made known) the Quran
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,"Taught him speech (language, modes of expression and communication)"
  55,5,The sun and the moon follow courses (exactly) reckoned (in space and time)
  55,6,And the stars (or herds of animals) and the trees do adore (Him)
  55,7,"And the heaven, He raised it high, and He made the Balance (or set the measure)"
  55,8,That you may not exceed the measure (or transgress beyond limits)
  55,9,But keep the measure strictly (with justice or equity) nor fall short of it (or be deficient in measuring)
  55,10,"And the earth, has He set out for (His) creatures"
  55,11,Therein is fruit and palms having sheathed clusters
  55,12,And the grain with its husk and fragrant herbs
  55,13,"Which then of the bounties (favours, gifts)) of your Lord will you deny"
  55,14,He created man from dry clay like earthen vessels (as containers)
  55,15,And He created the jinn of a flame of (or of smokeless) fire
  55,16,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,17,He is the Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests
  55,18,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,19,"He has made the two seas (streams or bodies of water, salt and sweet) to flow freely so that they meet together"
  55,20,Between them is a barrier which they do not transgress
  55,21,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,22,There come forth from them pearls and coral
  55,23,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,24,And His are the ships reared aloft in the sea like mountains
  55,25,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,26,All that is therein (on earth) must pass away
  55,27,And there remains naught but the Countenance of your Lord of Might and Glory (or of Majesty and Nobility (Bounty and Honour)
  55,28,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,29,All those who are in the heavens and the earth entreat (or need) Him; every moment is He in a (new?) state of Glory (or wields universal power)
  55,30,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,31,"Soon will We apply Ourselves to you, O you two worlds (men and jinn or outer and inner, manifest and hidden)"
  55,32,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,33,"O assembly of the jinn and the men! If you are able to pass through the regions of the heavens and the earth, then pass through; you cannot pass through but with authority"
  55,34,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,35,"The flames of fire (to burn) and smoke (to choke) will be sent on you two, then you will have no defence"
  55,36,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,37,And when the heaven is rent asunder and then becomes red like red hide
  55,38,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,39,So on that day neither man nor jinn shall be asked about his sin
  55,40,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,41,"The guilty shall be recognized by their marks, so they shall be seized by the forelocks and the feet"
  55,42,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,43,This is the hell which the guilty called a lie
  55,44,"They go circling between it and hot, boiling water"
  55,45,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,46,And for him who fears to stand before his Lord are two Gardens
  55,47,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,48,Containing in them various kinds (trees and delights)
  55,49,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,50,In both of them are two fountains (or streams) flowing
  55,51,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,52,In both of them are two pairs of every fruit
  55,53,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,54,"Reclining on beds, the inner coverings of which are of silk brocade; and the fruits of the two gardens shall be within reach"
  55,55,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,56,In them shall be those who are chaste with restrained glances; whom neither man nor jinn shall have touched before them
  55,57,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,58,As though they were rubies and corals (or pearls)
  55,59,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,60,Is the reward of goodness other than goodness
  55,61,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,62,And besides these two are two other Gardens
  55,63,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,64,Both dark-green in colour (the colour of foliage well watered)
  55,65,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,66,In both of them are two springs gushing forth
  55,67,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,68,In both are fruits and date-palms and pomegranates
  55,69,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,70,In them are goodly things and beautiful ones
  55,71,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,72,Pure ones confined to pavilions
  55,73,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,74,Man has not touched them before them nor jinn
  55,75,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and rich carpets of beauty
  55,77,Which then of the bounties of your Lord will you deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the name of your Lord, Mighty and Glorious"
  56,1,When the Inevitable Event comes to pass
  56,2,There is no denying that it will come
  56,3,"Abasing some, exalting others"
  56,4,When the earth shall be shaken to its foundations
  56,5,And the mountains shall be crumbled
  56,6,So that they shall be as scattered dust
  56,7,And you shall be sorted into three classes
  56,8,First the companions of the right hand - what will be the companions of the right hand
  56,9,And then the companions of the left hand - what will be the companions of the left hand
  56,10,And those foremost (in faith) will be the foremost (in the Hereafter)
  56,11,These are they who are drawn nigh (to Allah)
  56,12,In the Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,A multitude of those of old
  56,14,And a few of those of later times
  56,15,On thrones decorated
  56,16,"Reclining on them, facing one another"
  56,17,Round about them shall serve youths of permanent freshness (immortal or never altering in age)
  56,18,With goblets and ewers and a cup filled from a pure fountain
  56,19,"They shall not suffer with headache thereby, nor shall they get intoxicated (or exhausted)"
  56,20,And fruits such as they choose
  56,21,And the flesh of fowl and any as they desire
  56,22,"And pure, beautiful companions"
  56,23,The like of the well-preserved pearls
  56,24,A reward for what they used to do
  56,25,They shall not hear therein vain or sinful discourse
  56,26,"Except the saying, \"Peace! Peace"
  56,27,And the companions of the right hand; what of the companions of the Right Hand
  56,28,Amid thornless Lote-trees
  56,29,And tall trees with clusters of flowers (or fruits) one above another
  56,30,And spreading shade
  56,31,And water flowing constantly
  56,32,And abundant fruit
  56,33,Neither intercepted nor forbidden
  56,34,And exalted thrones
  56,35,Surely We have created them into a new creation
  56,36,And made them virgins pure
  56,37,"Loving friends, equals in age"
  56,38,For the sake of the companions of the right hand
  56,39,A multitude of those of old
  56,40,And a multitude of those of later times
  56,41,And those of the left hand; what of those of the Left Hand
  56,42,In hot wind and boiling water
  56,43,And the shade of black smoke
  56,44,Neither cool nor honourable
  56,45,Surely they were before this made to live in ease and plenty
  56,46,And they persisted in the great violation (or great sin)
  56,47,"And they used to say, \"What! When we die and have become dust and bones, shall we then indeed be raised"
  56,48,Or our fathers of yore
  56,49,"Say, \"The first and the last"
  56,50,Shall most surely be gathered together for the appointed hour of a known day
  56,51,"Then shall you, O you who err and call it a lie"
  56,52,Most surely eat of a tree of Zaqqum
  56,53,And fill your bellies therewith
  56,54,Then drink over it boiling water
  56,55,And drink as drinks the thirsty camel
  56,56,This is their entertainment on the Day of Requital
  56,57,"We have created you, why do you not then assent"
  56,58,Have you considered the seed (or what you emit)
  56,59,Is it you that create it or are We the creators
  56,60,We have ordained death among you and We are not to be frustrated
  56,61,That We may transfigure you and make you grow into what you know not
  56,62,"And certainly you know the first growth, why do you not then reflect"
  56,63,Have you considered what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you that cause it to grow, or are We the cause"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could crumble it to powder, then would you lament"
  56,66,Surely we are burdened with debt
  56,67,Nay! We are deprived
  56,68,Have you considered the water which you drink
  56,69,"Is it you that send it down from the clouds, or are We the senders"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could have made it salty; why do you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you considered the fire which you strike
  56,72,"Is it you that produce the trees for it, or are We the producers"
  56,73,We have made it a reminder and a convenience for the dwellers of the deserts
  56,74,"Therefore, glorify the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  56,75,But nay! I swear by the setting (or falling or fading) of stars
  56,76,And most surely it is a very great oath if you only knew
  56,77,Most surely it is an honoured Quran
  56,78,In a book that is protected
  56,79,None shall touch it save the purified ones
  56,80,A revelation by the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you then hold this announcement in contempt
  56,82,And make denial of it your means of subsistence
  56,83,Why then do you not (intervene) when the soul comes up to the throat (of a dying person)
  56,84,And you the while look on
  56,85,"And We are nearer to it (the soul) than you, but you see not"
  56,86,"Then why, if you are not under Our authority"
  56,87,"Force back (the soul), if you are truthful (about your independence)"
  56,88,Then if he is one of those Near to Allah
  56,89,(There is for him) Satisfaction and Bounty and a Garden of Bliss
  56,90,And if he is one of those on the Right Hand
  56,91,"Then (the salutation) \"Peace to you\" from the companions of the Right Hand"
  56,92,"And if he is one of the rejecters, the erring ones"
  56,93,He shall have an entertainment of boiling water
  56,94,And burning in Hell
  56,95,Most surely this is a certain truth (or the Truth of Certainty)
  56,96,"Therefore glorify the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  57,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and the earth declares the glory of Allah, and He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  57,2,His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; He gives life and causes death; and He has power over all things
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last and the Evident (or Outer) and the Imminent (or Hidden or Inner), and He is Aware of all things"
  57,4,"He it is who created the heavens and the earth in six periods, then He firmly established Himself on the Throne (of authority); He knows that which goes deep down into the earth and that which comes forth out of it, and that which comes down from the heav"
  57,5,His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth; and to Allah are (all) affairs returned
  57,6,"He causes the night to enter in upon the day, and causes the day to enter in upon the night, and He is Aware of what is in the heart"
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and spend out of what He has made you heirs (or trustees); for those of you who believe and spend shall have a great reward"
  57,8,"And what reasons have you that you should not believe in Allah? And the Messenger calls on you that you may believe in your Lord, and indeed He has made a covenant with you if you are believers"
  57,9,"He it is who sends down clear revelations upon His servant, that he may bring you forth from darkness into light; and lo! For you Allah is most Kind, Merciful"
  57,10,"And what reason have you that you should not spend in Allah´s way? For Allah´s is the inheritance of the heavens and the earth. Not alike among you are those who spent and fought before the victory (and those who did not): they are more exalte"
  57,11,"Who is there that will offer to Allah a goodly loan that He may double it (or increase it many fold) for him, and he shall have an excellent reward"
  57,12,"On that day you will see the faithful men and the faithful women, their light shining forth before them and on their right hand, (and it will be said,) \"Good news for you this day: Gardens beneath which rivers flow, to abide therein,\" That is th"
  57,13,"On the day when the hypocritical men and the hypocritical women will say to those who believe, \"Wait for us, that we may borrow a light from your light\"; it shall be said, \"Turn back and seek a light.\" Then there will separate them a w"
  57,14,"They will cry unto them, \"Were we not with you?\" They shall say, \"Yea! But you caused yourselves to fall into temptation, and you waited and doubted, and vain desires deceived you till the ordinance (punishment) of Allah came, while the Arc"
  57,15,So today ransom shall not be accepted from you nor from those who disbelieved; your abode is the Fire; it is your patron and evil is the destination
  57,16,"Has not the time ripe for those who believe that their heart should submit to the remembrance (or the Reminder) of Allah and to what has been revealed of the truth? And that they should not become like those who were given the Book before, but the term wa"
  57,17,"Know that Allah gives life to the earth after its death; indeed, We have made the revelations clear to you that you may understand"
  57,18,"Surely the charitable men and the charitable women and those who set apart for Allah a goodly portion, it shall be doubled for them and they shall have a noble reward"
  57,19,"And those who believe in Allah and His Messengers, these it is that are the truthful and the faithful ones in the sight of their Lord: they shall have their reward and their light, and as for those who disbelieve and reject Our revelations, these are the"
  57,20,"Know that the life of this world is only sport and play and idle talk and boasting among yourselves, and a rivalry in the multiplication of wealth and children; like the vegetation after rain, whereof the growth pleases the husbandmen; but then it withers"
  57,21,"Hasten to forgiveness from your Lord and to a Garden the extensiveness of which is as the extensiveness of the heaven and the earth; it is prepared for those who believe in Allah and His Messengers; that is the grace of Allah: He gives it to whom He wills"
  57,22,"No evil (or disaster) befalls on the earth nor in your own souls, but it is in a Book before We bring it into existence; surely that is easy to Allah"
  57,23,"So that you may not grieve for what has escaped you, nor be exultant at what He has given you; and Allah does not love any arrogant boaster"
  57,24,"Those who are niggardly (or hoard) and enjoin niggardliness (or avarice) on men; and whoever turns back, then surely Allah is He Who is the Absolute (Self-sufficient), the Owner of Praise"
  57,25,"Certainly We sent Our messengers with clear arguments, and sent down with them the Book and the Balance that men may conduct themselves with equity; and We have sent down Iron, wherein is mighty power (or War) and advantages to men, and that Allah may kno"
  57,26,"And certainly We sent Noah and Abraham and We gave to their offspring the gift of prophecy and the Book; so there are among them those who go aright, but most of them are transgressors"
  57,27,"Then We made Our Messengers to follow in their footsteps, and We sent Jesus, son of Mary afterwards, and We bestowed on him the Gospel, and We put in the heart of those who followed him kindness and mercy; but monkery (or monasticism), they invented it"
  57,28,"O you who believe! Be careful of your duty to Allah and believe in His Messengers: He will give you two portions of His mercy, and provide for you a Light with which you will walk, and forgive you, for Allah is Forgiving, Merciful"
  57,29,"So that the followers of the Book may know that they do not control aught of the grace of Allah, and that Grace is in Allah´s hand. He gives it to whom He pleases; and Allah is the Lord of abundant Grace"